  "editorial_writing_mandate": {
    "philosophy": "Write like a beauty editor at Byrdie or Allure — knowledgeable, warm, and authoritative without being distant. The reader should feel like they're getting advice from a friend who happens to know everything about nails. Every sentence earns its place. This is a magazine, not a blog farm.",
    "anti_templated_writing": {
      "rule": "The post must never feel templated, patterned, or AI-generated. It must read as if the best writer for this specific topic sat down and wrote it with full knowledge of the audience and intent. No two sections should feel like they were produced by the same formula. The reader should never sense a system behind the writing.",
      "how": [
        "Every section opens differently — in angle, in length, in register — using a different technique from the opening_engine",
        "The depth and pace of each section is determined by what the reader needs at that point in the post, not by a fixed word count per section",
